The paper deals with the dissemination of information in a network, which is a classic topic in computer science. The use of random walks and percolation theory suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) category. The focus on mobile networks and communication graphs suggests that it may also belong to the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) category. The use of mathematical models and analysis suggests that it may belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) category. The consideration of the physical reality of radio transmission suggests that it may belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) category. Finally, the tight bounds and characterization of the broadcast time suggest that it may belong to the cs.MA (Machine Learning) category.
